Q. How are the greens?
PADRAIG HARRINGTON:  Good. Very good in the morning anyway. They will be soft I am sure so it will be very tough for the guys in the afternoon. I thought they were fine. I hit a good putt on the last and it missed. Missed one on the first and the last and didnÃ¢ï¿½ï¿½t really miss any in between.
Q.  There were some nice shots out there?
PADRAIG HARRINGTON:  Three iron into the ninth to about three feet. Hit some good shots. Just a couple of careless shots there which knocked me back two of three shots which is a bit of a problem.
Q. Was the extra day a blessing?
PADRAIG HARRINGTON:  I was very happy to sleep all day yesterday. Definitely. It was a bonus for me to have the day off.
Q.  Do you build on today?
PADRAIG HARRINGTON:  Oh yes. I will go and hit a few shots and hopefully it will get better. It was a pity to let a couple of shots go. Four under is a lot better than two under.
Q.  Was it easy to keep your mind on the job?
PADRAIG HARRINGTON:  Yes. When you are out there doing your job it is no problem. I would have liked to have been but we always want to be better.
